|<poem>Son giunchi che piegano
le spade vendute:
già l'Aquila d'Austria
le penne ha perdute.
Il sangue d'Italia,
il sangue Polacco,
bevé, col cosacco,
ma il cor le bruciò.</poem> 
|<poem>[[Sabre|Mercenary swords]],
they're feeble reeds.
Already [[Reichsadler|the Eagle of Austria]]
Has lost its plumes.
The blood of Italy,
the [[Partitions of Poland#"Fourth Partition"|Polish]] blood
It drank, along with the [[Cossacks|Cossack]],
But it burned its heart.</poem> 
